@NODE Examp2 "Examples"
Examples:

1.Ram Disk:> MrSPLIT c:copy O=1024 ram:smallcopy
    This will cut out an area from the file "c:copy" from position 1024 to the
    end of the file. Stores the cutfile as "ram:smallcopy".

1.Ram Disk:> MrSPLIT c:copy O=1024 S=100
    This will cut out an area of 100 bytes from the file "c:copy" at the
    position 1024. Stores the cutfile as "ram:copy".

1.Ram Disk:> MrSPLIT c:copy sys:hello
    Copies "c:copy" to "sys:hello".

1.Ram Disk:> MrSPLIT c:copy S=3000
    Splits the file "c:copy" into smaller files with the filesize of 3000
    bytes each. Stores the files as "ram:copy0", "ram:copy1" ...
@ENDNODE
@NODE improve "Help me to improve MrSPLIT"
As you might have noticed, MrSPLIT is very basic. Why no fancy extras?

Well, we programmers have a very difficult job. We can program, but we
don't know what the general public wants. Some programmers makes
applications that suits their own needs, and some have visions. I on the
other hand don't make any applications for myself, I do it for YOU.
So now it's up to you to tell me what you expect from the next version of
MrSPLIT. I think that this is the best way to go in order to improve MrSPLIT.

If you have such ideas or suggestions, @{"send me email!" link contact}
@ENDNODE
@NODE registration "How to register MrSPLIT"
Registration is completely free and is done by @{"sending me an email" link contact} telling
me that you use MrSPLIT. I would also appreciate if you would tell me
with OS-version and CPU that you got. This will enable me to be sure of
which systems that MrSPLIT works on. Please also write your nationality, it's
always nice to know where in the world I have my users.

But do note that there is NO special registrated version, I will simply add
you to my user-database so that I can send you mails about new versions of
MrSPLIT, and to study when I need encouragement ;-)
All information that you send me will ofcourse be strictly confidential.
@ENDNODE
